	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Okay, as a Paladin (44 currently), I've recently maxed both my skills at their pre-50 cap of 200. I've been using a Wurmy (25 40) and a BABS (24 39) and to tell you the truth, the Wurmy flat out kicks the BABS' butt. The BABS has been getting better marks, but still doesn't reach the full power of the Wurmy. From what I've noticed, the BABS will hit consistantly in the 40-50 range with scattered hits from 20-90. The Wurmy, however, hits easily in the 55-70 range with nothing ever below 20 and some going into the 100's. But, here are the real issues: <BR>
<BR>
BABS: 2.5 wt | Wurmy: 15 wt<BR>
You just can't swing that Wurmy for very long. By the time I have a mob down to where it wants to run, I'm hitting about half as often as when I started. But with the BABS, there is zero stanima loss and I'm always hitting at peak speed.<BR>
<BR>
2HS BABS: 3svPoison | 1HS Wurmy and my shield: 25AC, 12STR, 5STA, 5svMag<BR>
I think the reason the Wurmy is doing so much more damage is beacuse of that extra STR from the weapon and my shield. 12STR is significant enough to cause a noticable difference in each hit. If you want to test this for yourself, find a kind shaman, druid or enchanter and have them give you a STR buff... then see how much more damage you'll be doing per swing. Unless I'm given a decent STR buff, I rarely, if ever, hit in the 100's with either weapon. But tonight, with ~150 unbuffed STR, a STR of Stone (15-20 STR, DRU), Yaulp II (20 STR, my own), and some bard song(10-15 STR, maybe some attack too), I was hitting in the 100's noticably more than usual. (On a side note, I think I remember seeing my atk at 930-940/1000 when all buffs were going).<BR>
<BR>
So I think I've blabbed on enough here... I think wheter or not you use 1 or 2 HS depends on what weapon is better, and what you'll be using it for (Wurmy is NOT good for fights longer than 2 min unless you have someone throwing an Invigor at you). I didn't go into fast/slow weapons because I have no experience with them as of yet. (What's a good fast pally weapon?)<BR>
<BR>
Hope this helps some of you :) Please file your complaints and flames in the round cabinet at the side of my desk and I'll get to them as soon as it's convenient.<BR>
<BR>
Ruvana Soulsaver &lt;Revixi&gt;<BR>
Paladin of the 44th Trial<BR>
Solusek Ro
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
