			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have had a lot of experience with using a 2-hander vs a 1-hander. my main is currently a level 53 Ogre SK. I have an Ardent Protector (42 dmg 49 delay w/ 25 str 15 int / wis mana &amp; hp 2hs w/ good dmg bonus &amp; other stats) With it, at 53, I double for any damage from 110-230. This, combined with my Cloak of Flames makes for insane damage, as I can easily deal out 400 damage a round, and can put down my foes in an extremely quick manner, nevermind Riposte. Also, I hit, or at least swing, every 2.695 seconds. With it, I have never lost a duel, and never plan to, so the choice of weapons between 1hs and 2hs all depends on how much cash you have to spend, who your guild is (if you're uber you can get Palladius' Axe of Slaughter and deal a ton of damage, but, if all you can afford is a weighted axe, I'd suggest going with one-handers as they are usually cheaper and can still deal their share of damage.)<BR>
<BR>
Thats my 2cp,<BR>
  Guardd Dawgg<BR>
53rd Shadow Knight<BR>
 The Shadow Order<BR>
   Lanys T`Vyl
