			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Wanted to post a little info of my own. Currently (12 -15 -01) the damage bonus on 2hs and 2hb has been significantly raised, with a 32 36 2hb at 57th I generally double attack for anywhere from low 60's to mid 170's (I have a damage bonus of 25), it's fairly decent damage and it also seems as though 2hand agro value has been raised. Duel wielding a 9 /18 and 9 /20 pair of weapons, I generally deal around 40-49 primary, and 20-38 offhand, with duel weild and double attack going off fairly often. In the long run, 2handers deal more damage, however as a tank you need to use the lowest delay weapons you can get to mantain agro, which is why many higher level melee duel wield instead of using 2handed style. Anyway, it's less about which to use the most often, it's more about situational planning, if you are main tanking, I would say 2handers all the way, but if you need to maintain agro, definatly duel weild. Hope this has been a little helpful tidbit of info for you wondering the ansewer to 1hs vs 2hs.<BR>
<BR>
Brel Lin'Darkmoore<BR>
Mrymidon of Rallos<BR>
<BR>
(ps) When in Pvp, use two handers on melee, that way every hit that gets through is worth it (ie: hits hard), vs a caster you should always duel weild to to intterupt, and use ranged weapons such as bows if they are running (duel weilding a caster with a DS hurts though..so make sure to pumice them first).<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

