			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I currently am a halfing warrior (17) with 110str 97sta 100agi and 99dex, so I miss a lot less.  I dual wield BALS (10/29) and crystal fiber (8/26) both extremely nice weapons for my level.  Since I dual weild about 1/5 of the time, and double attack about 1/5 of the time, and triple attack about 1/20 of all those times, and I hit for an average of 17 (max 21) with my main and 15 (max 20) with my offhand, I total about 480 or so damage every 58 seconds.<BR>
<BR>
When my damage cap lifts, i have a babs I'm going to use, 24/39 really nice!  I had a ranger friend who at level 20 started hiting for about 50 max, and averaged about 30 i would guess.  That means that in 58 seconds I could get in 14 hits minimum since I would dual weild about 1/5 of the time I would get three in so 18 hits for 30 which equals 540 damage (note that his babs increased to about 60 damage, and this was with a dex of 73 (quite pathetic!) hence I would probably hit for about an average of 40, which means 720 instead of 480.  It truly depends on what weapons you have, what is better kodiac claws (11/29) and bals (10/29) or rusty two hander (9/50 or something) it all depends on the weapons.
				</font>
			</td>

